headline: TSMC Says 'No More' To Nvidia: Why That Is Intel's Golden Ticket
summary: The AI boom just hit a constraint investors don't talk about enough: you can't ship what you can't build. Demand for AI chips is still surging, but the world's leading foundry, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co Ltd (NYSE:TSM), or TSMC, is starting to run out of room. That matters — because when supply, not demand, becomes the bottleneck, the entire power structure of the AI trade begins to shift. headline: Trump at Davos, Netflix earnings, SCOTUS hearing: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime Host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come next week, including earnings results from companies like Netflix (NFLX), Procter & Gamble (PG), and United Airlines (UAL); President Trump's attendance at the 2026 World Economic Forum (WEF) in Davos, Switzerland; the US Supreme Court's (SCOTUS) hearing on whether the Trump administration has the power to remove Federal Reserve governor Lisa Cook; and November's reading on the Personal Consumption Expenditures index (PCE). To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
